</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukerryndarkwater.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kerryn Darkwater</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1884<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/24/02 8:28:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3488.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Arserag neighbors</span><hr size=1> You're first mistake was giving the guy your phone number because now it's easy to complain for him and you can't ignore him.<br>
<br>
Barring this I would have suggested you just carry on and not answer him. Let him call the police and have them tell him he's out of order.<br>
<br>
Don't call the police in for his truck. At the moment they are on your side but as soon as you start using them in an attempt to play games that help will dissolve. They have the right to stop you both making noise and where will that get you?<br>
<br>
My advice would be to phone the police and explain the predicament. Give them the name of the officer that was good to you, and explain that both he and your landlady felt the music was not at an excessive level. At this point they'll note it for the files. Ask them for their advice.<br>
<br>
Then the next time he rings up to complain say this &quot;Both the landlady and the police do not feel that the music I am playing is excessively loud but please feel free to call them if you have proof to the contrary. In the meantime I intend to continue as this is my livelihood&quot;<br>
<br>
When he calls the landlady he only naffs her off. When he calls the police they will have it noted that he is being a problem caller and they will deal with it. <p><CENTER><A HREF="http://ak.lonelygamer.com">
<IMG SRC="http://www.plattsflello.com/ryn.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udunwutspeeritnite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dunwut Speeritnite</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.holystorm.org/boardstemp/stormshield.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/24/02 8:46:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3488.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Arserag neighbors</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> they shouldn't have to listen to you play the piano for 8 hours a day.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't think he was saying that he plays every hour every day, I believe he was saying he only does his composing at times between noon and 8pm.<br>
<br>
 <p><br>
<img src=http://www.theholystorm.org/gifs/dunwut-banner.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utovectris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tovectris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/24/02 8:50:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3488.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Arserag neighbors</span><hr size=1> In order, plus some more information:<br>
<br>
Toxx: True enough, raw emotion can be a useful addition to any composer's arsenal. I've not lost my love of writing through much more detrimental circumstances, incuding an explosion that cost most of my right-hand mobility and ability to play at any level for a couple of years. This guy won't be the end of anything, for sure.<br>
<br>
Gloriana: I don't play 8 hours a day, by any stretch. As a matter of fact I do most of my plinking in the wee hours of the morning with headphones on. On a good day I play no more than 30-45 minutes in the daytime, just to listen with full resonance what I wrote the night before on headphones. Since I've lived here I've not even attempted to play during the day more than a few times, each of which was squashed. I've not been able to play more than 3 hours straight at any time since the explosion, just to clear that up.<br>
<br>
Barrymore: Thanks, and I will =)<br>
<br>
Kerryn: You're right, I should never have given him my number, but I thought it was a good idea at the time for several reasons. I thought that once he learned that I wasn't just jamming to the Eagles or something and actually writing he'd change his views on it a wee bit. That was also the suggestion of the really cool police officer, and following his suggestions seemed like a good course of action. I do keep a log of everything I do to fix the situation. I keep track of his calls, the steps I've taken to quieten the room, and the money I've spent on the foam and other dampening equipment. This was also the officer's suggestion. I have contemplated telling him pretty much exactly what you put in the post, though my nature is not to impose on him at the moment. It'll come to a critical point at some time in the near future, and the repeated calls and my repeated attempts to remedy ther situation without bothering the police or landlady can only help to strengthen my case. I can still do more, and until I've done it I won't bring them back into it. Regarding his truck, you are right there. I haven't called yet, and I actually probably won't. It's nice to blow off steam now and then though.<br>
<br>
Dunwut: Close. I compose 24 hours a day. I play the piano in the middle of the night to see if those ideas work. I play them with full openess during daylight hours. If they're good I record them between noon and 8pm.<br>
